\title{Guidelines for potential contributors}

\p{Despite the title, we welcome a fairly broad range of contributions. Both in
other related \em{synthetic} mathematics, such as domain theory or algebraic
geometry; but also formalisations in the general theory of HoTT. In order to
easily formalise these synthetic mathematics it is important to have a strong
foudnation of results in HoTT and in \em{set-level} mathematics.
If you are unsure about what contributions would be welcome, feel free to ask us
on our [Discord server](https://discord.gg/Jfxv4jPTva).}

\p{Concepts should be contained within their own subtrees, with an appropriate
taxon, and in all but the most simple cases should come with an informal
mathematical description of the lemma/definition/theorem, as well as a sketched
informal proof if appropriate. It is important to remember that the forest
should be considered of equal importance as an artifact as the Agda library
itself. Consequently, we may also accept \em{partial formalisations} where
certain results are only defined or proved informally without accompanying Agda
code.
}

